FT  20 NOV 92 / Walt Disney improves by 29%
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By KAREN ZAGOR
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
WALT DISNEY yesterday posted a 29 per cent improvement in fourth-quarter net
income to Dollars 223.7m (Pounds 150m), on revenues which rose 21 per cent
to Dollars 2.08bn, writes Karen Zagor in New York. A year earlier, Disney
had net earnings of Dollars 174.1m. For the full year, Disney had net income
of Dollars 816.7m, up from Dollars 636.6m. In contrast to Euro Disney,
operating income from Disney's domestic theme parks and resorts soared 44
per cent in the quarter to Dollars 213.9m on revenues which rose 26 per cent
to Dollars 996.2m. For the year, operating income and revenues rose 18 per
cent, to Dollars 644m and Dollars 3.31bn respectively.
