<BYLINE>
   By DAVID OWEN and RICHARD LAPPER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
LEADING Names said yesterday they were optimistic that Lloyd's, the
insurance market, will extend the terms of a recent six-month debt
moratorium.
Earlier this month Lloyd's said that more than 3,000 Names, facing heavy
insurance losses, would be give an extra six months to cope with 'temporary
insolvency' but 172 Names who have already received writs demanding they pay
their debts did not benefit from the measure.
Action groups of Names, the individuals whose assets back underwriting, have
been pressing Lloyd's to extend the moratorium and Mr Alfred Doll-Steinberg,
chairman of the Gooda Walker Action Group said after meeting Mr Peter
Middleton, Lloyd's chief executive, he was 'strongly optimistic' that that
would happen.
