<HEADLINE>
FT  20 NOV 92 / Fears on council contracts calmed
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE GOVERNMENT yesterday moved to reassure companies which contract to
provide local council services that they are not affected by new regulations
protecting workers' pay and conditions when they transfer to the private
sector.
The regulations, which stem from a European Community directive, mean that
the pay and conditions of staff cannot be cut when there is a transfer of
undertakings.
Mr Michael Forsyth, the employment minister, said yesterday the new
regulations did not alter the legal position of people working in the
private sector whose work was contracted out. In a reply to a parliamentary
question, he said that the regulations applied only where there was a
transfer of an undertaking or part of an undertaking.
