<TEXT>
UKRAINE'S first computer engineering centre was opened this week in the
capital, Kiev.
Officials hope the centre, supplied with more than Dollars 1m (Pounds
600,000) worth of IBM computers and software, will help Ukraine's collapsing
manufacturing industries make the leap to modern technology.
The Computer Integrated Manufacturing Centre (CIM), based at the Kiev
polytechnic institute, will teach students and retrain professional
engineers in computer industries, design and manufacturing.
Ukraine is a world leader in cybernetics research and has a huge, and
under-employed, scientific and engineering community.
IBM, has supplied 14,000 personal computers to schools in the former Soviet
Union and
opens an office in Kiev this week.
