<TEXT>
THE QUALITY of seawater at Britain's beaches has improved slightly this
year, although a fifth of bathing areas are still below EC standards, the
government's 1992 survey of bathing waters shows.
The report says that 79 per cent of the 455 identified bathing places met EC
coliform - or bacteria - standards. This compares with 76 per cent in 1991
and 77 per cent in 1990.
