FT  19 NOV 92 / Sweden ratifies EEA treaty
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   STOCKHOLM
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Sweden's parliament yesterday voted decisively in favour of a treaty
creating the European Economic Area, Reuter reports from Stockholm.
The EEA will comprise the 12 EC countries plus members of the European Free
Trade Association: Austria, Finland, Iceland, Liechtenstein, Norway, Sweden
and Switzerland. If ratified by all, the treaty will permit the free flow of
people, goods, services and capital in an area from the Arctic to the
Mediterranean from January 1.
