<HEADLINE>
FT  19 NOV 92 / CU plans expansion after return to profit
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD LAPPER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
COMMERCIAL Union, the composite (life and general) insurance company,
yesterday announced that it is back in the black and said it is raising
capital to pave the way for further expansion.
Pre-tax profits for the nine months to September 30 were Pounds 6.1m,
compared with a Pounds 42.4m deficit for the same period last year.
The improvement in the third quarter was particularly strong, with pre-tax
profits amounting to Pounds 19.6m.
Mr Paul Found, group financial controller, said the results 'clearly
confirmed an upward trend', while Mr Tony Brend, chief executive, said the
recovery had been pronounced in the UK where pre-tax profits amounted to
Pounds 33.3m over the nine-month period, compared with a loss of Pounds
21.2m.
The group is launching a Pounds 100m cumulative irredeemable preference
share issue, the second time it has turned to the markets this year. The
issue will allow CU to continue its expansion in life assurance, as well as
write additional non-life business in order to take advantage of increasing
premium rates.
The preference shares, for which Hoare Govett and Cazenove are joint
brokers, will pay a net dividend of 8.375 per cent. CU's last issue paid a
net dividend of 8.75 per cent.
CU, the UK insurer least affected by losses from mortgage indemnity
business, has increased business at a steady pace. Non-life premium income
increased to Pounds 2.46bn (Pounds 2.14bn), a rise of 12 per cent in
underlying terms, while life premium income grew to Pounds 1.30bn (Pounds
945.5m) in the nine months. Premium income in the UK market rose 25.3 per
cent to Pounds 1.10bn.
Investment income amounted to Pounds 212.4m (Pounds 209.9m), after charging
external loan interest of Pounds 35.1m (Pounds 37.6m) and the costs of
non-insurance activities of Pounds 4.9m (Pounds 4.2m). Underwriting losses
were cut to Pounds 302.3m (Pounds 338.1m), with UK losses down from Pounds
157.7m to Pounds 128.6m.
Non-life operating losses of Pounds 75.9m (Pounds 123.1m), were offset by
life profits of Pounds 82m (Pounds 80.7m). Earnings from associated
undertakings amounted to Pounds 14m (Pounds 5.1m). Shareholders funds
increased by Pounds 96m over the nine months to Pounds 1.3bn.
</TEXT>
