Sir, In his review of An Ideal Husband (November 13) Alastair Macaulay
described me as 'never a convincing actor'.
'Never' is a big word to apply to a career spanning 54 years, and would only
be appropriate if he had seen me as Paris in Troilus and Cressida in 1938
and in my subsequent 50 West End appearances. Can he be so old?
Michael Denison,
Globe Theatre,
Shaftsbury Avenue,
London W1
