FT  19 NOV 92 / Observer: Big Spender
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Yet another sign of hard-pressed times, stagnating economies and collapsed
consumer spending yesterday: Britain's home secretary, Kenneth Clarke,
approved prize increases for public slot machines.
Now their limits are Pounds 3 for a cash prize (formerly Pounds 2.40) and
Pounds 6 for a non-cash prize (up from Pounds 4.80). Obviously designed to
pull in holidaymakers otherwise tempted by Las Vegas.
