<HEADLINE>
FT  19 NOV 92 / Brussels probes Del Monte deal
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The European Commission is to hold an inquiry into the acquisition of Del
Monte Foods International by the Imerman family investment consortium and
Anglo American Corporation of South Africa.
The deal involves an Imerman sub-consortium and an investment consortium
controlled by Anglo-American setting up a joint voting arrangement to
control Royal Group Holdings, which in turn will control Del Monte, the
Commission said.
Interested third parties have 10 days in which to file comments during the
first phase of the month-long inquiry under the EC's merger regulation.
