<HEADLINE>
FT  18 NOV 92 / International Company News: PWA files CDollars 1bn suit
against Air Canada
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
PWA Corporation, the holding company of Canadian Airlines International, has
filed a CDollars 1bn (USDollars 784m) lawsuit against Air Canada for alleged
predatory pricing practices, Reuter reports.
Mr Rhys Eyton, PWA chairman, and Mr Kevin Jenkins, president of Canadian
Airlines, claimed that Air Canada had 'dumped' extra airline seats on the
market this year in an effort to use its deeper financial resources to drive
Canadian out of the market.
'PWA Corp and Canadian Airlines have been aware of Air Canada's actions for
some time, but have now gathered key evidence to support this filing of
charges,' PWA said in a statement. PWA said the suit was filed yesterday in
an Alberta court.
Air Canada officials have previously denied such allegations, but yesterday
declined to comment on the suit.
Mr Eyton said the PWA charge was not related to the recent lawsuit by the
Gemini Group systems venture against PWA.
Gemini, which is jointly owned by PWA, Air Canada and a United Airlines
affiliate, recently sued PWA for CDollars 1.5bn.
Mr Eyton added PWA had few options if its proposed deal with AMR and
employees of its Canadian Airlines unit fell through.
He appeared to rule out renewed merger talks with Air Canada.
'We've wasted probably six months discussing merger possibilities with Air
Canada during the past year,' he said.
'We will not waste time and be taken down futile paths.'
</TEXT>
