PROFITS OF Cosalt, the Grimsby-based diversified industrial group, fell 24
per cent to Pounds 1.88m pre-tax for the year to August 30.
However, the total dividend is maintained at 10.75p, via a final of 6.5p.
Earnings per share worked through at 11.1p (15.05p).
The shares rose 7p to 143p yesterday.
Mr Bill Wood, finance director, said the group was now in a healthy position
